column1: NGR is from 1950s record, the elevations does not quite match but it is at the bottom of the bank as described in the 1920s record. The gauge moved from the top of the bank to the bottom in 1926 an elevation change from 1360 ft. to 1280 ft. and this appears to be a move of 200 to 300 yards probably SW from the upper reaches of Holly Moss Bank
May 1919 reading noted as being corrected for tampering, the reading has been removed along with the annual total
Jan and Feb 1940 readings are noted as being apportioned for snow, entered as -999 with annual total left in the record
